  "texts": [
    "For s ≥ 1, the predictions of F 3 become more and more overdispersed as s grows, and this large variance brings the dispersion of the ensemble close to the truth; however, beyond a certain point, the ensemble predictions become more dispersed than the truth.",
    "Thus, forecaster 3 maintains its top ranking in the importance until s reaches approximately 2.4.",
    "Thereafter, the ensemble formed without forecaster 1 generates forecasts with high dispersion, which results in the forecaster 1 having the highest importance metric among all models.",
